00:01:48.133 --> 00:01:52.067
Now I wanted to point out that
this subject we're dealing

00:01:52.067 --> 00:01:56.433
with now, I think, is one of the
four great paradigm shifts

00:01:56.433 --> 00:01:59.000
in the earth sciences.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:03.000
The four, in my mind, being the
theory of evolution, that

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:07.333
is, Darwin's idea of
the mutability of

00:02:07.333 --> 00:02:11.900
species back in the 1860s.

00:02:11.900 --> 00:02:14.233
The theory of the Ice Ages,
which we've spoken about in

00:02:14.233 --> 00:02:15.567
this course.

00:02:15.567 --> 00:02:20.100
The idea that just 14,000 years
ago, we had a thick

00:02:20.100 --> 00:02:24.833
layer of ice covering over much
of what is today open,

00:02:24.833 --> 00:02:27.233
useful land.

00:02:27.233 --> 00:02:31.867
The theory of plate tectonics,
which helps us to understand

00:02:31.867 --> 00:02:35.400
the layout of the continents,
how that has changed through

00:02:35.400 --> 00:02:36.467
geologic time.

00:02:36.467 --> 00:02:38.500
The difference between
continental crust and ocean

00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:41.900
crust. It even helps us to
understand the shape of the

00:02:41.900 --> 00:02:43.567
ocean basins.

00:02:43.567 --> 00:02:45.833
And then the theory of global
warming, which we'll be

00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:46.600
dealing with now.

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:50.400
Now, these each have their own
characteristics, but on a

00:02:50.400 --> 00:02:55.400
scientific front, they all
were true revolutions.

00:02:55.400 --> 00:02:59.300
In other words, they changed the
very most basic ideas of

00:02:59.300 --> 00:03:03.633
how we thought about the
different subjects of biology

00:03:03.633 --> 00:03:07.400
and climate and geology, and
then, not only climate for

00:03:07.400 --> 00:03:13.367
global warming, but also the
role of humans on the planet.

00:03:13.367 --> 00:03:15.433
There are books, interesting
books, written on the history

00:03:15.433 --> 00:03:18.267
of each of these.

00:03:18.267 --> 00:03:19.067
Fascinating reading.

00:03:19.067 --> 00:03:22.767
How they were resisted, how they
were promoted, what kinds

00:03:22.767 --> 00:03:27.167
of evidence finally tipped it
over so that the majority of

00:03:27.167 --> 00:03:31.233
the scientific community
finally accepted these.

00:03:31.233 --> 00:03:34.200
Fascinating reading in the
history of human thought.

00:03:34.200 --> 00:03:36.367
Of course, the theory of
evolution was resisted

00:03:36.367 --> 00:03:40.367
strongly by the church at that
time because it changed the

00:03:40.367 --> 00:03:45.667
way we thought about humans
and human nature.

00:03:45.667 --> 00:03:51.367
Still resisted to this
day in some areas.

00:03:51.367 --> 00:03:53.767
The theory of the Ice Ages and
plate tectonics I don't think

00:03:53.767 --> 00:03:59.900
had any kind of resistance or
even that much notoriety in

00:03:59.900 --> 00:04:01.833
the general public.

00:04:01.833 --> 00:04:05.867
So they were mostly battles
fought within cadre of

00:04:05.867 --> 00:04:07.100
scientists.

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:11.300
So that's a little different.

00:04:11.300 --> 00:04:13.367
But then we get to the theory
of global warming, and now

00:04:13.367 --> 00:04:17.967
we're back in a subject that
is of great interest to the

00:04:17.967 --> 00:04:22.267
general public as well, and
comes straight into politics.

00:04:25.633 --> 00:04:27.933
And it has a stake,
a current stake.

00:04:27.933 --> 00:04:30.500
Now, all of these things were
interesting--those first three

00:04:30.500 --> 00:04:35.067
were interesting intellectually,
but none of

00:04:35.067 --> 00:04:39.933
them required that we do much
in response to whether the

00:04:39.933 --> 00:04:41.967
theory was accepted or not.

00:04:41.967 --> 00:04:44.867
Where the theory of global
warming is a little different

00:04:44.867 --> 00:04:49.367
because it has to do with not
only the role of humans on the

00:04:49.367 --> 00:04:51.933
planet and the question of
whether there are too many

00:04:51.933 --> 00:04:55.000
people and our lifestyle is
wrong, but also in many

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:58.600
respects it brings in the issue
whether we should be

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:02.800
changing our lifestyle or
changing the way we do things.

00:05:02.800 --> 00:05:03.733
So here we are.

00:05:03.733 --> 00:05:07.267
And so you and I are living
through this one.

00:05:07.267 --> 00:05:10.033
Not only is it a scientific
debate, but it has these

00:05:10.033 --> 00:05:12.467
political and economic
consequences.

00:05:12.467 --> 00:05:16.800
It's really a mess, because
it's all these fears of

00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:21.933
discussion are engaged in the
theory of--in the discussions

00:05:21.933 --> 00:05:24.000
of the theory of
global warming.

00:05:27.733 --> 00:05:31.033
Any comments or questions
on this?

